message: Hello, my name is Alex, how can I help you today?
This is the second time I’m contacting you. My withdrawal is too slow, and I’m getting really frustrated! Where's my money?
I completely understand how frustrating delays can be, and I sincerely apologize for any inconvenience caused. Let’s check the status of your withdrawal now.
Before we proceed, I need to take you through security. Can you confirm your date of birth, registered email address, and postal code?
Sure, my date of birth is 12/05/1985, email is user@example.com, and postal code is 12345.
Thank you for verifying. Let me check your withdrawal details.
Just to confirm, your withdrawal of $500 is currently being processed and should be completed within the next 24 hours. I sincerely apologize for the delay.
It’s taking way too long. I needed that money sooner.
I completely understand, and I truly apologize for any inconvenience. As a possible resolution, I’ll escalate this to our payments team to see if we can speed it up for you.
Alright, I hope you can sort this out quickly.
We’ll do our best to resolve this promptly. Thank you for your patience, and feel free to reach out if you need any further assistance.
